100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 20, 1926, notable world events included the ongoing debate in the United States over Prohibition, as public sentiment increasingly favored repeal amid rising crime rates and illegal speakeasies. In Europe, the League of Nations continued efforts to mediate disputes, particularly concerning the tense relations between Germany and France. Meanwhile, political unrest in Egypt persisted, with protests against British rule intensifying as nationalist sentiments grew.
